<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{6}{y}=-{30}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}-{4}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({4},-{1}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{6}{y}=-{30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}=-{30}-{\left({6}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{30}-{\left({6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{\left(\frac{{-{30}-{\left({6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{6}}}}\right)}+-{4}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{3}}{{-{{6}}}}\cdot{\left(-{30}\right)}--\frac{{3}}{{-{{6}}}}{\left({6}\right)}{y}+-{4}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{15}-{\left(-{3}\right)}{y}+-{4}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{y}+{\left(-{4}\right)}{y}=-{8}--{15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{y}+{\left(-{4}\right)}{y}={7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3}+{\left(-{4}\right)}\right)}{y}={7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{y}={7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{7}}{{-{{7}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{1}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{6}{\left(-{1}\right)}=-{30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{\left(-{6}\right)}=-{30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}=-{30}-{\left(-{6}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}=-{24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{24}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={4}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({4},-{1}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

